	   <tr><td colspan=2>I completely agree with the people that say this is another example of the poor Everquest design that requires camping.<br>I love quests, and I think they are a big part of Everquest, a part that differs it from lame RPGs like Diablo II. However, I wouldn't call this a quest. I would call it one big Everbore. Same goes for Testament of Vanear. Is this what you call fun? This is not a quest, this is a game design bug as far as I'm concerned. Nobody should waste hours of hours for hunting those Ghasts. A quest is about talking to NPCs, being involved in storyline, advancing towards the item by getting information from various sources, not sitting in a middle of a forest clicking Track, then Cancel, Track, Cancel. These so called quests are the worst thing in Everquest today.<br>&nbsp;<br>Marblond Beastmasterr<br>52nd Season Druid of Morell-Thule</td></tr>
