	   <tr><td colspan=2>The rancorous Ghasts will spawn more frequently if you keep the roaming undead cleaned out. If you are trying to avoid the notice of the Brownie scouts however, this could be a devastating tatic. I would check into Lesser Faydark every 3 hours or so during low usage times and find them. When the server is heavily populated, find a central location, like pos 500, pos 1000, which is the center of the zone, and wait for one to spawn, someone is always killing the undead off. Of course, being a level 22 Druid with maxed out tracking ability helps. A couple of things I can tell you for sure. First, it is about a 50 percent rate that one will drop a heart, and the second thing is that they alway spawn in pairs. If you find one, the second one is there somewhere, unless it got taken by another hunter.<br><br><br>Uanamien Pinebough<br>Draco Odium<br>Terris Thule<br>&nbsp;<br>Uanamien Pinebough<br>Draco Odium<br>Terris Thule</td></tr>
